        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 26 at 2:30PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 230 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northeast of Pritchett, or 11 miles northwest of Springfield,
moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Two Buttes Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
